cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

The paper discusses a novel network architecture for computer vision applications that incorporates non-linear morphological operations. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions that the proposed network can be trained using traditional deep learning techniques, indicating that it may also belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of structuring elements, which suggests a possible fit with sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
